03/05/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor vowed on Sunday (May 2nd) to tighten measures against football hooliganism in light of clashes Saturday. 
In all, 15 police officers and six football fans were injured during and after a match between the Dinamo (Zagreb) and Hajduk (Split) at Zagreb's Maksimir Stadium. 
One police officer was seriously injured by a firework and lost an eye. 
Police detained 91 fans. 
Property damage included five police cars, two buses and two trams. 
(Radio Free Europe, Nova TV, Vecernji list, HRT, Index, AFP - 02/05/10)
